  "prompt": "How do I get Indian dental health data?",
  "response": "To obtain Indian dental health data, you can try several sources:\n\n1. Government Sources:\n- Ministry of Health and Family Welfare\n- National Health Portal of India\n- Indian Dental Association\n- National Health Systems Resource Centre\n\n2. Research Databases:\n- PubMed\n- Google Scholar\n- World Health Organization (WHO) databases\n- Indian Council of Medical Research (ICMR)\n\n3. Survey Reports:\n- National Family Health Survey (NFHS)\n- National Sample Survey (NSS)\n- Annual health surveys\n\n4. Online Resources:\n- Research papers\n- Academic journals\n- Government health reports\n- Statistical websites\n\n5. Direct Contact:\n- Dental colleges\n- Public health departments\n- Research institutions\n\n6. Specific Data Sources:\n- Oral Health Survey Reports\n- State-level health databases\n- Research publications focusing on dental health\n\n7. International Organizations:\n- World Health Organization\n- UNICEF\n- Global health research networks\n\nRecommendations:\n- Cross-reference multiple sources\n- Check publication dates\n- Verify data credibility\n- Consider regional variations\n\nThe most comprehensive and reliable data will likely come from official government and research institutions.",
